definition.value: A MemberProgram defines a loyalty (or membership) program that provides its members with certain benefits, for example better pricing, free shipping or returns, or the ability to earn loyalty points. Member programs may have multiple tiers, for example silver and gold members, each with different benefits.
A MemberProgramTier specifies a tier under a loyalty (member) program, for example "gold".
A men's clothing store.
A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.
A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.
Enumerates several kinds of product return policies.
A MerchantReturnPolicy provides information about product return policies associated with an [[Organization]], [[Product]], or [[Offer]].
A seasonal override of a return policy, for example used for holidays.
A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.
A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).
A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.
A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.
Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use [[PriceSpecification]] Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.
A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.
A monetary grant.
The act of transferring money from one place to another place. This may occur electronically or physically.
A loan in which property or real estate is used as collateral. (A loan securitized against some real estate.)
A mosque.

A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
A motorcycle or motorbike is a single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.
A motorcycle dealer.
A motorcycle repair shop.
A motorized bicycle is a bicycle with an attached motor used to power the vehicle, or to assist with pedaling.
A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.
A movie.
A short segment/part of a movie.
A movie rental store.
A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.
A movie theater.
A moving company.
A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.
A museum.
A collection of music tracks.
Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.
The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.
A musical composition.
Event type: Music event.
A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.
A collection of music tracks in playlist form.
A music recording (track), usually a single song.
A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.
Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).
A music store.
A music venue.
A music video file.
Organization: Non-governmental Organization.
NLNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the Netherlands.
